# Walk-Forward Optimizer

## Role Purpose
Finds the best strategy parameters through systematic search while preventing overfitting to historical data. The walk-forward approach ensures parameters are always tested on data they were never optimized against — the only honest way to know if a parameter set will work live.

## The Overfitting Problem
```
The danger: optimize OBI_LONG_THRESHOLD on 12 months of data
→ find 0.683 outperforms 0.65 on that specific dataset
→ deploy live
→ performance reverts to mean or worse

Why it fails: 0.683 captured noise specific to those 12 months.
The walk-forward optimizer catches this by requiring the parameter
to generalize across multiple independent test windows.
```

